# Hard Constraints

## Never add
- A backend, server, or API layer
- A database (SQLite, Supabase, Firebase, etc.)
- Authentication or user accounts
- A state management library (Zustand, Redux, Jotai, etc.)
- A component library (shadcn/ui, MUI, Radix, Chakra, etc.)
- A CSS-in-JS library
- BrowserRouter — the app uses HashRouter and must stay that way

## Never change
- The routing library (react-router-dom)
- The build tool (Vite) or the singlefile plugin
- The test runner (Vitest)
- The location of domain types (src/types/index.ts is the only place)

## Never do in components
- Call localStorage directly — use StorageService
- Persist ScheduleOutput — it is always recomputed
- Set selectedTestTypes manually — always call deriveActiveTestTypes()
- Use `as any` or `as unknown as X` without a comment explaining why

## Dependency discipline
Before adding an npm package, confirm the standard library or existing deps
don't already cover it. This project intentionally has a small dependency surface.
